OL,3,CPolice force pays #9,000 in damages to
OL,4,Cveteran for 'false imprisonment'
OL,6,FHe launched a civil action against the
OL,7,FChief Constable of GMP and a hearing
OL,8,Ftook place in May this year when a
OL,9,Fjudge at Manchester Civil Court
OL,10,Fallowed his claim for unlawful arrest
OL,11,Fand false imprisonment, awarding him
OL,12,F#8,746.52 in compensation and costs of
OL,13,F#35,000 against GMP.
OL,15,FAt a separate hearing a month later,
OL,16,FGMP requested leave to appeal the
OL,17,Fruling, but it was refused. However,
OL,18,Fthe Chief Constable has now applied to
OL,19,Fthe High Court in a bid to get Judge
OL,20,FKhan's decision overturned. A date has
OL,21,Fyet to be fixed for that hearing.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/9
