OL,4,Cveteran for 'false imprisonment'
OL,6,FHe claims that as well as spending
OL,7,Fyears attempting to clear his name
OL,8,Famid the 'stigma' of being a rape
OL,9,Fsuspect, he told police about medical
OL,10,Fevidence which showed he suffers from
OL,11,FPeyronies Disease, which he says
OL,12,Frenders him physically incapable of
OL,13,Frape.
OL,15,FThe former Royal Military Police
OL,16,Fofficer has served in Northern
OL,17,FIreland, Bosnia, Afghanistan and Iraq.
OL,18,FDuring his career, he was attached to
OL,19,Fthe Foreign and Commonwealth Office
OL,20,Fand worked in numerous British
OL,21,Fembassies worldwide.
